    "body": "If I'm reading it right, you have disk _read_ at `5.47 MB/s`, and write at `3.63 MB/s`. Those speeds are comparable to if your disk is attached via usb 1.1. Which is to say, that is a very slow disk. If it is an SSD, it's extremely deteriorated -- SSDs tend to do that over time. \r\n\r\nI don't think you will ever complete a sync on that disk. \r\n\r\nYou could also try this, to get a \"second opinion\" on the write-speed. :\r\n```\r\ndd if=/dev/zero of=./tmp_output conv=fdatasync bs=384k count=1k; rm ./tmp_output\r\n```\r\n",
