    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I see. Well, for quite some time now, syncing on an hdd has been \"basically not supported'\" - the disk speed required to perform a sync won't be reached on an hdd. You need a faster disk, I'd recommend and NVMe ssd disk. You can use an hdd tor `--ancientdir`, i.e. where geth stores some of the not-so-hot data, which is somehwere around 400GB which doesn't need to sit on the 'fast' disk. \r\n\r\nThe model says `QEMU HARDDISK` - which sounds to me like it's a virtual emulated disk ? Meaning, hard to say what's the actual backing storage. \r\n\r\nBut doesn't really matter -- it's not sufficient. Not much more to investigate here, I'll close this. ",
